[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Kings 2:1-2",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 2:1-2",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The days of David drew nigh, that he must die — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As he himself was sensible. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And he charged Solomon his son — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "After the example of Abraham, the father of the faithful, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 18:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I go the way of all the earth — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Even the sons and heirs of heaven must ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "go the way of all the earth, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "of all who dwell thereon. But they walk with pleasure in this way, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "through the valley of the shadow of death. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Prophets, yea, kings, must go this way to brighter light and honour than prophecy or sovereignty. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Be thou strong — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For, to govern his people according to the law of God, required great fortitude or strength of mind. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And show thyself a man — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In manly wisdom, and courage, and constancy, though thou art but young in years.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2:1-4 David's charge to Solomon is, to keep the charge of the Lord. The authority of a dying father is much, but nothing to that of a living God. God promised David that the Messiah should come from his descendants, and that promise was absolute; but the promise, that there should not fail of them a man on the throne of Israel, was conditional; if he walks before God in sincerity, with zeal and resolution: in order hereunto, he must take heed to his way.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
